2.00	Pierre_Langois	The Black Dahlia Murder (band)	The Black Dahlia Murder is an American heavy metal band from Waterford, Michigan, formed in 2000. Their name is derived from the 1947 unsolved murder of Elizabeth Short, often referred to as Black Dahlia. The band comprises vocalist Trevor Strnad, guitarists Brian Eschbach and Ryan Knight, bassist Ryan "Bart" Williams and drummer Shannon Lucas. Out of their five studio albums, the latest four of them charted on the US Billboard 200, with 2009's Deflorate peaking at #43 and their latest album Ritual reaching #31.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/36/The_Black_Dahlia_Murder_collage2.png/220px-The_Black_Dahlia_Murder_collage2.png
